\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Well me father had just turned seventy-when he died. He always said he wanted to live 'til old age pension and that was seven - it was seven and six was it or ten shilling, seven and sixpence then, he always said, I d
on't care, he said, I can go, he said, I would love to see old age pension. And he did live - live 'til - just a bit after it, he were died seventy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How old were you when he died?
