\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well it were in first world war. The war. It must have been because I c
an remember him coming home to see me when he come over on leave, when he come home, and our Elsie were - on't table with me mother like and she were hanging clothes up with bootlaces, he didn't seen her, well you see t'other - our Nellie come afore then.
 Our Nellie's the oldest in them two. There's fourteen month in them two. And then there were - our Elsie and then the oldest that died. My oldest is Elsie now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Your father was seventy when he died?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 He were about seventy - nearly seventy when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Do you think he would be about thirty-five when you were born, was it during the '14 - '18 war that he died from dropsy?
