piece of bread and cheese he'd all go day. He loved his bit of - block of cheese at side of the fireplace with whole pint of tea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh yes, you know - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No. We never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When could you leave the table? Had you to ask or had you to wait until everyone had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, used to say - can I go now mother? I've done. Aye, go on, you can go if you've done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well - ther
e sometimes wasn't 'em all at home you see. You know what I mean, someone'd perhaps be working - and the others might be just going to work. Same as - one'd be coming home at two o'clock, other one'd be happen two 'til ten. Well see they went to work diff
erent turns you see. So actually she were at it nearly all - all the time with - food like and that, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Sometimes your father wouldn't sit at the table, he'd sit by the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 With cheese and bread and a pint of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 He loved
 his - he used to love his - say, there's stuff on table, he wouldn't, I want my bit of cheese he'll say. Sitting by the fire, he didn't want to move. And they were never without a fire. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 
I know her used to say, George, shall I put your chair out front room yonder, front door, get a bit of fresh air. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
No, girl worrying, he said, I'm all right where I am. He said - no you couldn't budge him. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How was the meal served, by whom, did your mother always serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How did she do it, did
 she get all the food out of the pans and put them onto the plates and give you a plate, or did she used to put it into tureens and put the tureens on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes, that's way she used to - no, she didn't no. She used to empty 'em in - to a - a dis
h, and put 'em in the oven - to store down you know, and then she used to say - now who wants potatoes? You see, I want some mother please. Well you'd ask what wanted and then - do you want some greens or potato - cabbage or - anything like that. Well you
'd all ask for it and I - I'm not going to put it on your plate if you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 won\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
 eat it. And she'd put what they want on then she gave 'em all their dinner together eat together you see. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Can you remember your sister or the twins being little, and how 
they managed for their meals? Did they have a high chair at the table, or did they sit on your mother's knee for their meals or would they sit in a pram and have it there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well, tell you the truth she used to have one in a pram and one in a chair, sh
e used to give 'em together. And feed them both together, you know, here for one and then other one. She had a struggle I'll tell you. She had, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 It was always your mother who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Aye, always. Never had liked to disturb all us meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would you say that your mother was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Oh yes, she were right pleasant. Oh she'd sit and she listened, and she'd take - things in, you know what I mean. You'd told it to her and didn't go to anybody else she'd listen to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did she show affection?
