\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well she practically would tell you. You know because, what's the matter mother? What's the matter now? No }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 nowt luv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 , I'm all right. She wouldn't tell you. She wouldn't upset you. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 If you had any worried could you tell her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh yes, I tell her. She said, now if owt was wrong you tell me. Owt goes wrong outside, anybody been talking, calling me or owt like th
at you know. There's a Mrs so and so's been chatting at me. So what did you say owt back to her? I said, no, I didn't say nowt back to her mother. I've come to tell you. She said, well all right, well stop in, don't go away any more. She wouldn't go and f
a
ll our with 'em. She said, well keep away, and if she says any more then I will and I'll go and have a word with her. And that's what she were like. She didn't believe in going out and - showing herself up and her business to everybody. She'd send for her
. To - to the home like, to where were living, and she'd have it out - with here then, just tell her, say, well leave my child alone. If she does anything wrong you just come and tell me, and I'll correct her. But like that, she wouldn't row with nobody.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 What about your father, would you say your father was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh he were John Bull, he didn't care nowt for nobody me dad were. He were a right jolly fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, he - no, he used to - everything were - lucky you know, he - he never used to bother. I don't know, happy go lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would you say that if you had any worries would you tell your father about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, wouldn't tell me father, I'd tell me mother. Go and tell me mother if owt h
appens, 'cos she would ask you, and she could tell in a minute with you - faces or owt if something were wrong. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well they expected us to be good to them. And we were good to them, we ne
ver give my mother a word back. Nor me dad. We were a family like that. We never used to bother with anybody, we used to keep ourself to ourself. We were independent in anything like that. It were always in mother's wish. She used to say, be like your mot
her. Don't bother with nobody and then you can't fall out over anybody. Now - she used to tell me all sorts of little ditties you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sister in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh aye. Oh we were a good family, never fell out as I know of. We'd nowt to fall out for though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh aye, yes, if anybody hit, me she said well then you tap 'em back. Said, stick up for yourself, wh
ich I used to - she used to say, I'll not be here to stick up for you. She used to say, now stick up for yourself, if you get the worst on it. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well - I can't say much about that but were - all brought up respectable, and we all tried to do for one another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh yes, they never put nothing at front of us, never to be, no. Me mother n
ever ever told me when her was poorly. She didn't know. We were frightened to tell her. I was. And me daughter - my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 lasses}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
 - my girls now - they're the same. Our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 Elsie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
 say and our Bess is happened to be poorly, what lived across here, she used to say, do y
ou know our Bess is poorly mam? I said, you what? She said, our Bess is poorer. I said, well she's not said nowt to me. She says, I know she hasn't but she's told me. That's - that's the way my - my girls is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Do you think there were certain things tha
t they hoped you would consider important in life, were there certain things about you? Do you think they brought you up to consider certain things in life as important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well I've never kept nothing back from 'em. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 You mean you'd to be honest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Oh yes. Oh I - if they were here they would tell you, I never - I've never had to thrash 'em nor nothing. Never tapped 'em. I've had a good family and a good lot, have been good to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 What did your parents think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well
 you hadn't - we hadn't to swear in front of her. If we did any swearing and - it was outside if you got mad you were - run around with somebody else you know sometimes - you know - anybody there, oh I never heard your Alice swear before, you know. She sa
ys, well let me hear her. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When grown ups were talking were you children allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Well we did sometimes used to say, no mother. Said, I'm not talking to you, now you talk when you're spoken to. That's what she'd tell, I'll speak to 
you when I've talked to this one. Oh she'd us all weighed up don't you worry. She had. But she tried to put you right whatever you wanted. She wouldn't put you into no trouble - no - want so and so and so and so, oh no, no. One of the best, my mother.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I did anything wrong and she wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 If she got to know about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 She got to know, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 What would she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh she'd set about you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 You'd get smacked would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
She might tap me, say, what have you been doing? What have you been doing again? And you'd say, well I've only been so and so. And she'd get hold of me hand and she'd give me hand a crack, she'd say, now - take that and don't do it no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would your father ever smack you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Oh no. We were never lathered. I don't remember of any of us being - 'cos we were we had to do it. We know what we had to say and what to do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Can you remember any particular occasion when she did smack you, and what it was for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
I only remember once this, and I was - I wasn't married, I were getting on, and this brother, what I'm telling you what died - Fred - I once said - it was in Orchard Place, corner of Orchard Place where we live
d then, and - he were a right 'un, he never - he never had nowt to eat and used to go to church every Sunday morning. And he catched me, mother says - wash us them - few - dishes up Alice before you go back to school. Oh I said, let our Lizzie wash 'em up
? I said, you always climb on me. Our Fred come and got hold of back of my neck here, he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 says}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
, you what? He said, don't use to that to your mother no more. He said, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
on't let me hear you so you going away looking. By God I run but I were glad to run down ro
und corner of street. He run after me to crack me. Because I telled him. Yes, oh - but he were a good living lad, he used to go to church every Sunday morning. He did when he was living I know 'cos I - I - I - look I couldn't have had a better father and 
mother. Worked hard all their lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When your mother had smacked you how did you feel about it, what did you think afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well that day I - I thought well I shouldn't have said what I did say. You know, you couldn't tell me it after, but I 
- I were a bit - I can remember it and I were - I were a bit - it seemed to be me, always me, you know, she used to say - Alice, she never said Lizzie. Lizzie go and do so - Alice come and do this, do that. You see, I were oldest and I were biggest, well 
I was stronger than her, a lot. I told her that our Lizzie should have it for a change. She said, what with that - he picked me up in a minute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a mo
re important part than the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Well I admit I were rough when I went to school, I were more like a lad. Aye, I was like a tom lad, they used to call 'em tom lad then. And - same as a - if I seed a - a boy - in the school yard - and - they were ri
bbing this little kid, now me I could chide 'em up, I'd have go up, hey, what are you doing that for, leave her alone, you're a lot bigger than her. Take your hands, off her. Then we'd get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 
up to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121  scrapping, 'til you get fetched in school and get caned for i
t. Now then, what have you been - what's - what's the matter now? Miss Fellowes they called her. She come from Sheffield. And she says, toe the line, we toed the line both of us, now - what's been going on? What have you been fighting for? I says, it's ha
d
 hold of a little girl like this, but I says it's head and shoulders bigger than her. Says, who was it, so I told her the name. So she fetched her in. And she says to her - toe the line, to her, she toed the line in front of her desk. She says - now then,
 
what have you been fighting for, in front of the others. She says, so and so, she said - she got behind me and tried to leg me down, she said. So I did do and I got up so I went for him to hit him back. She says - he started leathering me. She says and wh
a
t did you do Alice? I says, well I saw him hitting her so I went to him and telled him to leave off. I says, he were head and shoulders bigger than her, but I said, I never seem him let her down. Outside. Go on back to your place and don't let me get it a
gain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Do you think that your mother or your father gave you the ideas how you should behave? Who was the one who taught you how to behave? Your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well practically both on 'em. But they always did - we were always told - were 
taught to do. See mother were that good. So we never used to put no trouble at front on her. If you could help it anyway of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No. Sometimes you'd have one, sometimes you wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would you ever get a present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh aye, we used to have a little toy or something like that them days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would you have anything special to eat for tea perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, sometimes she'd make a little cake. A little cake for a little treat for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would you have any friends in to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Well - just one or two who we knew, went to school with. You know, perhaps next door neighbours, she lived next door. About half a dozen schoolchildren, make a little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2580133\charrsid12200121 tea party}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121  for us you know what she could afford.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day? What would you do on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well she used to make us - Christmas cake and mince pies and all such like as that. And my
 brothers used to go and get a drink. Sometimes they'd fetch me dad one, fetch me dad a drink, especially at holiday time like, but me mother wouldn't have nothing. She never drank nor smoked. And - she'd make what she could for us, you know. Aye. She see
d we had a bit of a do. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would there be any Christmas presents? Would there be a stocking or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well I - I don't think so, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 It would cost a lot for all of you wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 We had a Christmas card come fr
om relations you know, Christmas cards. But I don't remember - only having a present at the - in our stockings. They put all the stockings up. Well they were pillowslips and put what - they could get 'em at sixpence and ninepence a piece than you know. Fi
ll 'em up with oranges and apple and a new penny or something like that, what we could get off with. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 During Christmas Day do you remember ever singing carols or playing games or anything like that at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well you see - them as is oldest ha
ve been out. And there were only me two - me and me sister, we never used to bother much like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you ever have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No. No. No, we didn't luv.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Was there anyone in the family who could sing? NO? Did your parents ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Oh sometimes at dominoes and draughts and that. You know, at night time. When it were cold like and we didn't want to go out then we used to have a game of - dominoes and - draughts and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
