\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well I can't tell you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I think you said you got a little house before your husband went in the army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I was in a little house behind the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid208450\charrsid12200121 bake house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 . And - I had a little - our Annie, that oldest gi
rl, an then he went away and left me, and I were pregnant with me other baby. And he went from pit with three more - three more men. But I didn't know where he'd gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 He didn't tell you he was going?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 He didn't tell you he was going in the army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
No. He went from the pit, got word and went straight through to - Aldershot. I and there was three of 'em. Well I couldn't get to no - no one. I lived in this little house behind bakery, well I couldn't pay - me rent, I couldn't do
 nowt because I'd no - no money or nothing. So anyway - I go down to Town Hall where - soldiers was and I reported it to - officer. Oh he says, is that the case Mrs Scroop? I said yes it is. I said, he's been gone about - a month, I said, I don't know whe
r
e he is nor nowhere. I said, he went from pit, I said, in his pit clothes and all that, never changed himself nor nowt. And I said I've got three on 'em. Because all three went together and they never seen owt no more. Well - the old gentleman down at the
 
Hall where - soldiers were billeted - so I went down and seed him and - he give me a cheque to - rig me little lass out, you know, with shoes and that, and - anyway - he - he says, oh leave it to us Mrs Scroop, he says, we'll find him. Well he's away in A
l
dershot. Well I got all me back pay down, he says, you'll get your back pay, I says, well - I've had to give me little house up, I said, I couldn't pay me rent nor nothing. And I couldn't expect me poor old mother I says to do it for me. She's done enough
 
for me I think. So - he says, yes, he says, very good of her. So that was - so we'll find him, he says, and there's a - a - what did they call it, the Tommy ticket or something they called it, to go and rig - our Annie up. Clothes and that for her, and bi
t - something to eat. Because they were good to me when he went. But I got all me money down. I had a rough life while he were in the army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you go back to live with your mother then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes, I had to do because - I couldn't stop in me house you 
see I couldn't pay me rent. I wasn't getting a ha'penny from nowhere. Not while me - pension book come through and everything you see well they - they didn't know where he was - he was, well they had to find out where he was. Then they would have let me k
now you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 And then you started to get your pay every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 That's it, everything all - all serene like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Was it about 1914 when he went in the army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 That's right, first world it was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 The beginning of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes.
\par 
