\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I stayed there - yes, yes. My eldest was born then. And she was born and - I told you about him coming home didn'
t I? Then he went back. He stayed over his leave and - I told him he could come - to see me, he says, I'm very - very sorry Mrs Scroop he says - he's been over - over here with - his time. I said, well he went from here soon enough. Ah but he's been stayi
ng somewhere, he says, and that's the reason why he come to see his baby before he's gone over to France. I never saw him while - he come home for good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 So she was two was she? He saw her first when she was two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes, well she'd be round about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 That was Elsie, the second one. When he came home in 1918 did he come and live at your mother's with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 He come and stayed with me while war were over do you mean? When he come home for good? Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 He came to live at your mother's with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes, had to stop because we had nowhere to go you see. No place you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Then you bought another house did you, you got another house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes, and we managed to get one after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How old was your husband when you married him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well - he's two years and a half older than me. And I'll be eighty-one next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 So he would be about twenty or twenty-one when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Something like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When you got married at first you told me that your husband was a trammer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Had he always been a trammer from leaving school? Or had he done any other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh - no. No, he went straight to pit as far as I - I know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When he came out of the army what job did he go to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I think he went back into pit again, I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Was he a trammer again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well he wouldn't be a trammer then, he'd be different. I just forget luv that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Can you tell me briefly what he did between the end of the war and him dying, what sort of job
s did he do in that period? I know he worked at Cloughs for one period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh yes, he worked at Cloughs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 What was he doing at Clough's?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 He was in - what they called it, where they give 'em all - have to go for the stuff, what do they call 'em
? Where they go for brushes and all suchlike as that you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 Eeh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
 - well he used to - he used to have to look after that, look after this place, and lock up, lock it up. Used to come for all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 He was a storekeeper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 That's the thing. That's right, yes. I just couldn't get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 You can't remember any jobs he did at Rotherham, other than being in the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, not as I know of, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 You had to go out to work as soon as your children got a bit bigger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How did your husband feel about you going out to work? Did he not mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Well - no, he - he said I cold just go please myself. I tell him I said we can't manage on this? I said, I'll go and do a bit of cleaning or something like that. Well at Sunday morning I used to go
 and clean - the public houses, used to go and clean that out of Sunday morning. Just odd jobs like that. To help us out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Was this because he was out of work quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Was it because he was out of work quite a bit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well - he w
as out of work, we didn't get the money like, you'd depend on the pit giving them - what they call - a - a sub - sub - sub something they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Subsistence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How do you think your husband felt about his work, did he like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh I never heard him grumble. No, liked his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 You had eleven children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How many of these were born before 1918? Was it just two, Alice and Elsie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes. Yes, at wartime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 What year would it be when Alice was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Our Alice? Well that's first oldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Alice is the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, El - Elsie's the oldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 What year would she be born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I know it's in November. Yes, the tenth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 You were married in 1909, which was your first baby? Was Elsie your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Was Elsie your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, Annie. Annie what died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 And then Elsie, but Annie died so Elsie was the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you have them both at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh yes. Yes. I never had one at hospital. AND I never had an operation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Before you had Annie and Elsie did you know what to expect in childbirth? Did you know what it was going to be like having babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh I'd an idea, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Had your mother told you all about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 She told me like - to expect you had to be poorly, you know, and - few little details about it you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How did you get on having them? Were they easy births or difficult births?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh - it weren't very - oh it weren't bad, I took a 
long time in between. Because they were all big - they was - and - first baby were eleven pound two ounces. No. Me first were fifteen pound two ounces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Annie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No - the four what died you know. And - yes, he lived to be three month old, he died, 
and - and then - I buried - I buried - four girls, you know, one girl and three boys. And the last'n I buried was three year old, when he was in Moreton Banks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 That was when you came to Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes, he had to have him and two others in a week.
 Took him in at morning, I were - I had doctor to him and fetched doctor to him and - and it were on his throat. Well I fetched doctor to him, he sent him straight away. And then at Thursday they come and fetched my Dolly and - my Bess away, at Thursday. 
A
nd then - and then at Monday they - they come to fetch me, said I was - germ carrier. So - I was in and - my Dolly were in, we both come out together. But Bessie were in and she developed - scabies in her hands while she was in. So she was in there eleven
 
week. And she couldn't walk when she come out. And - I wanted to bring my little boy out at same morning. And Doctor Crocker come up, and she see'd the nurse, and the nurse said, I don't know what you - you're doing with - been doing with your little sonn
y
, Mrs Scroop. I says, why? He says, every time we give him his - meals, he says, he throws his pot and plate on the floor. Well I says, he never used to do at home. And he didn't. He was a good child. I says, he might have seen someone else do it else he 
w
ouldn't have done it. I'm not saying he's an angel no more than no other child, but I said I've never known him to do - he weren't brought up to it, I said. I said, but he did used to have an enamel plate. You know, I used to have - he did once break one.
 
And I said to his dad, I said, oh, I said, I'll - I'll get him an enamel mug and a little saucer and a - plate of his own you see. But do you know he knowed different. He said, I don't want that little plate mum. I says, why? He says, it isn't enough. So 
-
 so - I never laughed at him you know. So he says, well, he says, anyway, he says - Doctor Crocker - he should have come home that morning. So she says - I said, how's me family going in? Oh he says, they're doing fine, she says - right champion, she said
.
 Well at twelve o'clock Doctor Crocker come up to see us, he always come round about dinnertime. And he used to shout to me so we knew him you know. Well he said - you know, and our - our Doris she were in other room, she could see all what were going off
 
you know. First night they went in they had to let him sleep with her. Oh he raised the place down. Talk about upsetting. So - anyway - doctor come, he said, now Mrs Scroop, I'm sorry to tell you - say a prayer for little Billy, he says, there's no hopes 
for him. Well that put me back, and I've never been right since.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When you had Annie at home did a doctor come to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh yes, I had a - what did they call him, Doctor - well there was baby one and Doctor - Doctor Riddle, and Doctor - Carrie
r was it, Creagh, Creagh. Mm. They'd both the doctors. But more or less - me children being - born - me first 'un I tell you, that was such a big boy, well me youngest, that's our Bessie, she were eleven pound twelve born. All big babies. And me lad were 
a big lad and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did your husband help you having the babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Oh no, he wouldn't - he wouldn't - he was glad when I got it all over you know. Oh you wouldn't catch him seeing him doing nowt like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How quickly did you get out of bed after having them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Well them days we didn't get out of bed, it were ten days. Just depends how you was you see. But I had to try and make me way out, sake of the other children you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 After ten days did you get up for a full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
No - me mother said, when you feel tired go and lay on bed a bit, stop up there and make sure, or on your own bed. Because she had me bed at lower being like that you see. I had - I had to have both - both at me mother's. That's when he went soldier
ing you know, I told you about and - yes, yes. Had a good mother, she looked after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When you had Elsie she looked after Annie for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Annie there, she was as good as gold, she were good. I couldn't have wished for a better mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 So you wouldn't need any neighbours or anything to come in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
No. No, me mother could do that job herself. But she weren't certified you see. She could do all but - but she didn't do me 'cos being like - being her daughter. Been a stranger, you or anybody 
else she would have done it. But anyway she used to send straight away for - doctor to come, and midwife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you breast feed your babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I breast fed 'em all but one. All the lot, all the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you enjoy feeding them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh yes, I l
iked that, feeding 'em, yes. Me mother used to say come here and I'll feed him while you do so and so. Me mother loved children. Well she'd eleven of her own, good as twelve. You know, I already told you - only one as had a big family. She said, our - our
 
- our - our Alice takes after me, she's five, she's got biggest family what's married. Like the fourth oldest - third oldest girl now what's living. The youngest is fifty. 'Cos they're all getting up you know. The youngest is forty-three. What's living, b
ut our Billy - our Billy'd have been next, if he'd have lived, oh it broke me heart that. She said he were going on rising and champion and - and then to come and tell me they're doing all they can for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you have any difficulties in feeding them?
