ne when to ring up. So when I went - come back home I tell him what did owt about. So he said, well it's up to you. I said, well we'll let her go in. I said, I'm not going to have this - and she went in were nearly thirteen year old. Anyway we let her go 
in. She went in, she had an operation, and - you know, I could come up for - two or three minutes at night time, so we went up and she were laid there and she'd a - she'd a piece of wire - I call it wire, that - what do they call, the stitching.
