w much your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I couldn't tell you what at pit, I don't know what he earned. He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 never}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121  - he never let me know nothing, used to give me just home what - I had to manage on. And then tell you sometimes I had to - well - I used to go and hav
e a couple of days somebody'd ask me if I'd go and - would I do their washing, something like that so as I'd get a copper in between. Oh no, I never - I never made - I never had to cross - cross him. All my wages was thirty-five shilling. But - had }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121  wo
rkers, you understand. And he would be working on them you see. But the wages weren't like they are now. Well them four workers - well others and him, and he used to give me thirty-five shillings for the week. Well what cold I do with that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 It were the dau
ghters what were bringing - in that way for me, were all money, money, money, do you understand, he used to back horses - and often he'd go and have a drink with lad and suchlike, and I never used to bother, I were working, scratching me eyes to get work 
- to try to bring more - yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 So from getting married to him going in the army you never knew how much he earned, he never told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No. No, he were - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 So you don't know how much of his wage you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No. I didn't know what I was going to get tell you the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 It varied from week to week did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you ever discuss with him how the money should be spent, or was it left to you what you did with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well - he used to give me this money and I used to t
ry and make it out with - best I could out of it. I went - I'll just tell you something now, it's a bit long and - I went - me and him fell out - he fell out with me like, and he were right jealous man, I daren't go out anywhere. So anyway we fell out thi
s
 part week, and our lasses used to say give up on our mam, dad. If I went out to do shopping he'd swear blind I'd been with a man. He's like - were like that, a too jealous man. And he were a bit on that side when I were courting him. So - anyway - I neve
r
 spoke to him for about - oh about a week, or he never spoke to me and I thought to myself well - and that's when I turned. And I thought, well I don't see why he should throw me like this. I don't go out, I've done nowt wrong. And this is what I'm gettin
g
. So - anyway, it come Friday, 'cos we were on the dole, it come Friday. Of course he got his money, but the dole weren't it is today. So anyway - he gets his dole. He comes home in, he says to my oldest - he says to my oldest girl, Annie, I'll never forg
et it if I live to be a hundred, he says, Annie, he says, can the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4603364\charrsid12200121 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
 bake? She says no, she were only a young girl, she says, no, she says I can't bake. He says, why? She says, well you - he didn't like shorthand, anyway it were me baking bread you know, so a
nyway he said to our Annie - got a nice little set of drawers in corner, and he - he - sent our Annie, put it on a piece of paper, he said, write it down. Come on, go to shop for these, well - and I - so I never said a word. And he says - fetch a stone of
 flour, and that what you make bread with, I couldn't remember that, yeast. So }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4603364\charrsid12200121 go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
 and fetch some of that. And she fetched two pound of sugar, all what we wanted - and half a pound of pork dripping, it were dripping them days, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 butter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121  - well we had margar
ine, didn't have butter. You know, just what he thought I got in. Then - what I like, I used to try and get a tin of sommat, bit tasty for us you know. So - it passed on - it passed on nearly the week and this here flour on - oh glory be to God. He blowed
 the top of the roof off. He says - how long is that going to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4603364\charrsid12200121  be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
there? To me. I says, what? And I looked at him. I says, what? He says that in that bag. I says, I'm not baking it. And that's when I turned on him. I says when you start laying money out, I s
ays, I says, I'll bake it. When I got right money I says I'll bake. He's says well it's not stopping here. I said, it'll stop for me 'cos I'll never bake it. That's why he asked our Annie if she could bake. So I says, well as soon as you tip your money up
 and you give me your right money, to bring these children up, you get so much at dole and you put so much down. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 
And - he - I says, soon as you was to tip your money up, I said - you - I'll bake that flour and I shan't till then. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 And that stood there nearly
 another week afore he tipped his money up. And when next - the Friday after come in and he put his money on the table.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 And you bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4603364\charrsid12200121 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
