Well I wouldn't leave 'em do you see. I wouldn't leave 'em. I never did leave 'em, I've trailed 'em with me before I'd leave 'em. Because I' know they've been safe then. Know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When you and your husband }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6255762\charrsid12200121 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121  perhaps your mother were talking did you allow the children to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh no, no, I should say - if they come to talk to me I'll say, now wait a bit because I'm talking to your dad, something like th
at if I were saying owt special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 What did you bring them up to consider most important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you tell them that they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 To hit back? Oh I'd tell them to fight theirs
elf. I said, I'm not going out falling out with her. If you get worst end of it you get worst end. It were so - it weren't so bad then - if it were so bad then I would do. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Were there any children that you discouraged them from playing with for some reason?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
No. I used to let 'em go out like with others, long as there were no - trouble nor bother you know, falling out with 'em. Them days were like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 If one of your children did something that you disapproved of and you were cross 
about what would you do about it? Would you smack them or just tell them off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, I used to bring 'em in and send 'em upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 You didn't smack them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, I never hit one of me childer. I never remember me putting a finger on my family - a
nd nor their dad. And that was only one, and that was our Annie and they were blamed for something he hadn't done. Well it got to police, the police come and - and told us that - at - the school over here, and there were two of them and they both said - t
h
is young lad what went with him, and it were dinnertime, and my Alice what lives at Leicester, she says, where's our Henry mum? I says, he's not come home yet, I wonder what's the matter. So I - anyway goes up - in school. Well we waited, I says - you - y
o
u can go back - you can go back to - she were working then, you can go back to work, I said, and I'll wait for him coming. Well he come about half past one after her got back to work. Well dad says, well I'm not going back to work, he said, while I see my
 
lad in for his dinner. And so police who lived down here, one of these groves down here, and - Cromwell Road, and - he's died since and all he has - but anyway, go apart from that, and - oh hadn't they leathered him, school. When he come home - all his fa
c
e were - red - where they'd smacked him, they put third degree on to make him say that he took eight shilling out of school milk money. And him and his young - other young boy were all together, the two of them. So when he come his dad said, now what's th
e been doing? He said, dad I know - he said, I haven't done nowt, he says, they blame me for taking eight shillings from the school, and a bottle of milk. He said, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 what's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121  that on your face? He says, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 poll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
 - he says, policeman's done that, they called him }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2714250\charrsid12200121 Twig}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
, and - tap on his face 'cos he were - oh and it were swelled up with crying. Well he bolted round to the school, he said, I'm coming up bobby. And I thought he were going to hit the policeman. We could see into schoolyard over here you know. Anyway - he 
- he said, yes, that's the only trouble I've ever had with any, never - never had a summons or nothing with 'em. They've been a good family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 You usually set them up to bed if they'd been naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well I used to take her upstairs out of road else I'll kill you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from you and your husband or did they get it mainly from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh, from me. I brought 'em up same as me mother brought me up. Tried to do. We were br
ought up respectable, and knowed things were, all the lot of us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When the children were very small you didn't go out to work did you, or did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh no, no, when they got bigger. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I think you told me -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When are we talking about because I was thirteen when I left school. I told you that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Was it during the first world war that you went on munitions in Sheffield?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh yes, I was working up Sheffield when the bombs came first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Wasn't that the period - was that in the second world war was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 No, 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 And your mother looked after the children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes, yes. I had two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 How did you feel about leaving them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well I know they were left in good hands, else I wouldn't have left 'em. I didn't 
worry 'cos she'd have done anything for my family. Oh she were good to us all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Some people think that children should be with their mother all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Others think it's not necessary and does them good to be with someone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 'Course it does. I believe in that, yes. Just depend who they get amongst though, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 But with your mother you felt they were all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 I did, I thought the world of my mother, and me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 When your two eldest girls ha
d a birthday when they were very small would it be different from any other day, would they receive presents or have a special tea or anything like that when it was their birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Oh we used to buy sometimes buy them a little present, what we could afford to buy 'em you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Would they have anything special to eat at teatime, would they have jellies?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Sometime used to - if you had a good dinner didn't want a tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did they ever have any little friends in, was it a little party at 
all, did they have any friends from neighbours in for tea when it was their birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Oh - we used to make a little cake or - have a little cake and have 'em in the - in me mother's big room you see. And they just wanted what they wanted to come. Them as they used to play about with, let so and so come mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Can you remember when they were small what you used to do on Christmas Day? Would it be much as any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Well it were problem what to get for 'em all. Were a problem. They used 
to put a pillow slip up and - perhaps a new penny in the - bit of spice or - of course things weren't like they are now you know. Oh we had to do. What you pay for a penny now you pay two bob for - don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you ever have any musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Do what luv?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3230341 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 Did you ever have any musical instruments, a piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009002 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10504500\charrsid12200121 
Oh I - I did when I lived up at Groves. I had a - a lovely piano, and then we bought the lad, we bought him a - what do they call them things that -
